<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 12:00AM CDT  by NWS Goodland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Thomas
County through 1215 AM CDT...
At 1200 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Brewster, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Thomas
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
